What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Automotive Electronic Control Unit Market?

Market Analysis and Insights :

Global Automotive Electronic Control Unit Market

Automotive electronic control unit market will reach at an estimated value of USD 77.12 billion by 2028 and grow at a CAGR of 6.54% in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028. Rise in the safety standards in the automobile industry acts as an essential factor driving the automotive electronic control unit market.

Electric control unit (ECU) is defined as a device which is embedded in automobile that is responsible for regulation and alternation of a car’s electronic systems. These electronic systems can include fuel injection set-up, anti-lock braking system (ABS) among many other features. Rise in the demand among consumers for energy efficient consumer vehicles is an essential factor driving the market growth.

Rise in the incorporation of advanced safety, convenience, and comfort systems acts as a crucial factor accelerating the market growth, also rise in the demand for electric vehicles, rise in the demand for safety and comfort features in cars in North America, rise in the demand for electric vehicles in North America and Europe, rise in the production of autonomous and semi-autonomous vehicles in Europe and Asia-Pacific and rise in the awareness of energy efficient cars in Asia Pacific and Latin America are the major factors among others boosting the automotive electronic control unit market. Moreover, rise in the advent of concept cars and autonomous vehicles and increase in the rate of installation of advanced applications in luxury and mid-range vehicles will further create new opportunities for automotive electronic control unit market in the forecast period mentioned above.

However, rise in the consumer preference for Byod and operation failure in ECUs are the major factors for restraining the market growth, and will further challenge the automotive electronic control unit market in the forecast period mentioned above.

